[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837781926896&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837781926896&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

I have a (seemingly) straight-forward question about the proper
way to do address to name resolution.  As far as I can tell,
there are two methods:

	Do an inverse query given the address and class, such as:

		INVERSE(Class=IN,Type=A,Answer=1.2.3.4)

	Or do a query of the form:

		Query(Class=IN,Type=PTR,"4.3.2.1.in-addr.arpa")

First, are both methods legitimate?  Second, are all servers
capable of one mode or the other and if so which one?

Thanks,

-Philip

